                                 K U L T 

                         (Exxos/Ere Informatique)




The following five 'ordeals' must be completed within an hour!


THE TWINS.


When you enter, you will see the two Serpents.


Open both of them.


Enter the door to your left into the Fountain Room.


Inspect the Fountain.


Press the Eye.


Fill the Goblet with water.


Enter the room you just left.


Pour the water into the left-hand Serpent.


Take the Dice.


Throw it a few times - it will always be 2.


Put the Dice in the right-hand Serpent - the door facing you opens.


Enter the door facing you.


Touch and then press the Serpent's Head.


There are 7 hands.......you need to raise 2........there are two possible

alternatives.


Imagine the base in which the hands are stuck to be a 5 x 5 square, then

the two hands you need to raise are either both 1's or both 2's:



                                 * 1 * * *

                                 * * 0 * *

                                 2 * 0 * 2

                                 * 0 * * *

                                 * * 1 * *



Touch and press the Serpent's Head again.


Read the writing on the inscription that was hidden behind the sliding

partition.


Go into the Fountain Room.


Lift the cube that has the wavy lines carved onto it (Cube 6).



Viola! You have found a Skull!!



DE PROFUNDIS.


Wait on the Platform until it begins to sink.


Lasso the column that drops from the ceiling.


Grab hold of the rope.


Wait until the Granite Monster surfaces.


Jump onto it.


Wait and it will take you to the far side where you will find the Skull!!



THE NOOSE.


Unless you have the lantern, use Solar Eyes from your Psi Powers option.


Grab hold of the left-hand rope.


Pull the Lever to hang the Aspirant who stands on the platform.


Search the platform and find the Skull!!



IN THE SCORPION'S DEN.


Pray to the Statue.


Use Zone Scan from the Psi Powers option.


Enter the door facing you.


Crawl on the web.


Talk to the Spider Woman.


Show her the Fly.


Refuse to kiss and make love to her.


Give the Fly to the Blue Spider.


Leave the Room.


Put the Red Spider into the open Mouth on the Statue.


The trapdoor will now open.


Pass Kehle and you will get the Skull!!



THE WALL.


You must enter from the right-hand door (you face into His Master's Orbit

so it is behind you to the right).


Close the sliding wall completely.


Enter the door to your right.


Climb on the step.


Put the Dagger into the slot.


Enter the passage facing you.


Put your hand into the hole and get the Skull!!!





